<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="External_links">External links</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vishishtadvaita&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: External links"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul><li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.wisdomlib.org/hinduism/book/siddhanta-sangraha-sailacharya">The Siddhanta Sangraha, English translation</a> from the 18th century</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.wisdomlib.org/hinduism/book/a-history-of-indian-philosophy-volume-3/d/doc209953.html"><i><span title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit transliteration"><i lang="sa-Latn">Viśiṣṭādvaita</i></span></i> doctrine of Soul according to <i><span title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit transliteration"><i lang="sa-Latn">Rāmānuja</i></span></i> and <i><span title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit transliteration"><i lang="sa-Latn">Veṅkaṭanātha</i></span></i></a>, Surendranath Dasgupta, 1940</li></ul>
